history.content: It's always a good idea to preview slides and lectures for any class – even skimming the material will help give you points of orientation when you actually have to learn the material in depth. That sounds like a rough time considering that CS61B will be taught by Hilfinger this spring, and both Phys 7A and EE16A have a significant in-class time commitment due to labs. It definitely leans on the more difficult side, but if you feel that you have the intellectual maturity and study habits to match, I have seen (very few) people successfully pull off a similar workload.

Hello, I am a first-year and about to take EE16A, CS61B, and Physics 7A next semester. How is that schedule in terms of difficulty and should I study anything during winter break to help me prepare for the upcoming semester?
